<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99169498686796></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99169498686796><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99169498686796>RE: Is it worth it</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99169498686796#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=44704><span id= >AllenRomero</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 4th 6:49 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Is it worth it? IS IT WORTH IT? Obviously you don't see the benefits of the enchant metal series and the animation series, so I will explain this to you as simply as possible. I myself almost always solo, and even if I'm not soloing, having a fighter around that is the same level as your last spell level is great! There's nothing like the security of having someone watching your back as you meditate or loot corpses either. For that matter, enchanter pets are hands down the coolest in the game... We get a floating shield and weapon! Everyone else's pet has to have a body... And our pet counts as a magic weapon, too, so it can help you hunt willowwisps... Now, as far as the enchant metal series goes... Enchant silver's not that great, but if you are going to work jewelry, wouldn't you much rather make magic artifacts than simple baubles? Besides, some of the later enchant metal spells produce items that are in high demand. That means you can 'make' money by making a whole bunch of the artifacts and then selling them wholesale to other players! Cool!<br>Well, I hope that straitens you out, whippersnapper! Enchanters rule because of those two spell series (and tashani).<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp; --Emett<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
